		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName><sic>Pittsburg</sic></placeName> <date>September 9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1853</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">I was <sic>somwatte</sic> astonished to<lb/> see in News <sic>itemes</sic>&#44; in your last Occident the Election of a &#61;<lb/> <persName>Rev. Mr Rubinson</persName> in <placeName><sic>Richmont</sic> Va.</placeName> <sic>wich</sic> you announced<lb/> with such pleasure to your readers&#44;</p>
			<p>Now sir let me tell you that about five or six <sic>wheeks</sic> ago<lb/> <sic>ther</sic> was here a man who called himself <persName>Mr Rubinson</persName><lb/> Dr of Phi&#44; at that time <persName>Mr Rubinson</persName> in presence of<lb/> <persName>Rev Mr Mareuson</persName> Hasan of our congregation and<lb/> Gentlemen from <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> by the name of <persName>Mr Cohen</persName><lb/> Now in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> &#40;at <persName>Mr Goldschmits </persName>Tavern&#41;<lb/> both Israelites he denied <sic>possitivly</sic> that he was no<lb/> Israelite&#44; and as he expressed himself his father<lb/> a born <add>Hebrew</add> and has nothing to do with the Jewish<lb/> Religion&#44; and as far as I know <sic>dit</sic> not Lodge by<lb/> any <add>Hebrew</add> here&#44; but he <sic>dit</sic> know that <sic>ther</sic> was a<lb/> Jewish <sic>benefial</sic> society <sic>her</sic> <sic>wher</sic> he <sic>applid</sic> for benefit<lb/> but the <sic>Presitent</sic> of the society being apprised that he<lb/> has <sic>deniet</sic> of being a Jew told him the <sic>socity</sic> was only<lb/> and alone for poor <sic>Jewes</sic>&#44; to <sic>wich</sic> he said what<lb/> difference it could be to him what he was.</p>
			<p>Now sir let me ask you if such a <sic>intivitual</sic><lb/> as the one who was here in <placeName><sic>Pittsburg</sic></placeName> should be taken<lb/> up by any congregation what benefit will a congre&#61;<lb/>gation receive from such a character&#44; that is&#61;</p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>the way I look at it&#44; &#40;as I myself <sic>hav</sic> been traveling<lb/> for about seven years among <sic>Gentils</sic> but never <sic>deniet</sic> my<lb/> Religion&#41; I am only a <sic>comen</sic> man and <sic>hav</sic> <sic>verry</sic> <sic>littel</sic><lb/> or no learning&#44; but still it strikes me and makes me<lb/> feel <sic>verry</sic> anxious to see such a thing&#44; should be true<lb/> would not a congregation be better without Hasan<lb/> than to have such a one</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Now <persName>Mr Leeser</persName> as I know<lb/> that you are a <sic>gread</sic> man for promoting <sic>Jewdism</sic><lb/> among the <sic>Jewes</sic> and that you try your best to make<lb/> the <add>Hebrew</add> what they ought to be please and give <del>give</del><lb/> yourself a <sic>littel</sic> <sic>troble</sic> you will find <persName>Mr Cohen</persName> from<lb/> <placeName>Cincinnati</placeName> in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> and inquire of him <sic>abut</sic><lb/> what I wrote above&#44; that is if you think that I may be<lb/> only a <sic>littel</sic> right&#44; I may be wrong&#44; that is that a men<lb/> may do all those things and more too&#44; and still may<lb/> be taken up as Hasan and Lecturer in a Jewish cong<lb/>regation.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir I tell you <sic>cantitly</sic> that I am ignorant<lb/> in Religion matters&#44; I think I only know our common<lb/> every day practices&#44; all I wrote you that for<lb/> is that I could not help to think <sic>joust</sic> as I<lb/> wrote you&#44; your will be kind <sic>enouff</sic> and forgive<lb/> my <sic>ignorence</sic></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">With that I remain yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">N. Gellinger</persName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
